By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –   The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has confirmed 1,664 fresh cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria. According to the health agency, the new cases were reported from 23 out of the 36 states of the federation including the FCT. Lagos State- the commercial nerve centre and the epicentre of the novel virus infection recorded a whopping 642 infections followed by the FCT with 407 while Plateau came third with 160 cases. Others states where infections were reported (in hierarchical order) are as follows:Kaduna-83Rivers-62Adamawa-47Nasarawa-38Abia-29Edo-28Anambra-27Niger-24Ogun-24Imo-15Oyo-14Kano-12Osun-12Borno-9Delta-7Enugu-7Bauchi-5Ekiti-5Sokoto-5Jigawa-2. See the state by state breakdown of total confirmed cases below: By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria on Saturday recorded 110 new cases of COVID-19 infections, bringing the total confirmed cases in the country to 67,330, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control has said. This is also as the Centre has informed that a total of 62,819 patients have… November 29, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) -  Nigeria's confirmed COVID-19 infections figure shrunk to  58 new cases on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has said. According to the report released by the NCDC, the newly recorded cases brought the total confirmed cases to 59,345 out of which… October 5, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Precise Post) -   The national health agency in charge of COVID-19, Nigeria Centre for  Disease Control on Tuesday announced the confirmation of 296 new cases of the novel virus in the country. The agency reported that the new infections were recorded in 15 states of the… September 9, 2020 In "Top Stories"